The paper discusses the use of deep learning to train optimizers, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific task of training convolutional networks suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The use of variational loss and the focus on optimization also suggest neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY) as possible sub-categories.
